### Problem Description

https://github.com/elastic/elasticsearch/pull/142254 introduced a bug which can result in the intercepted query logic registering multiple async action consumers unnecessarily. This happens with `knn` queries that provide a "complete" query vector builder (i.e. doesn't infer the inference ID from queried `semantic_text` fields), and with `sparse_vector` queries that provide an explicit inference ID. What happens is:

- The intercepted query logic [creates a query vector supplier and registers a unique async action to set it](https://github.com/Mikep86/elasticsearch/blob/2da00124216accb5aecedacbc2175b9e151894d8/x-pack/plugin/inference/src/main/java/org/elasticsearch/xpack/inference/queries/InterceptedInferenceKnnVectorQueryBuilder.java#L214-L221)
- The intercepted query logic [gets inference info to determine the `semantic_text` fields queried](https://github.com/Mikep86/elasticsearch/blob/2da00124216accb5aecedacbc2175b9e151894d8/x-pack/plugin/inference/src/main/java/org/elasticsearch/xpack/inference/queries/InterceptedInferenceQueryBuilder.java#L353-L364). The `copy` operation does not copy the query vector supplier set above.
- In the next rewrite round, a new query vector supplier is created and new unique async action is registered. The async action is successfully deduplicated, resulting in one unique async action with two consumers. The first consumer (for setting the initial query vector supplier) is defunct.

Note that this does *not* result in multiple inference calls; the unique async action deduplication prevents this. At most, this results in a few extra rewrite rounds to set a valid query vector supplier.

### Steps to Reproduce

The problem can be reproduced with either a `knn` or `sparse_vector` query:

```
GET test-index/_search
{
    "query": {
        "knn": {
            "field": "dense_vector_field",
            "query_vector_builder": {
               "text_embedding": {
                 "model_id": "my-dense-vector-model",
                 "model_text": "foo"
               }
            }
        }
    }
}

GET test-index/_search
{
    "query": {
        "sparse_vector": {
            "field": "sparse_vector_field",
            "query": "foo",
            "inference_id": ".elser-2-elasticsearch"
        }
    }
}
```

